---
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../../config";
import "../../styles/global.css";

const projectName = "Manufacturing/Product Ops Copilot for Profitability and Utilization";
const projectTagline =
  "A private, on prem LLM workflow that turns operational signals into a structured SITREP and an executive ready slide outline.";
const projectSummary =
  "Unlisted case study prototype for Amkor Tempe, built to align with the Product Engineer Intern posting for advanced packaging, flip chip BGA, and chiplets.";
const pageType = "Case Study";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>{projectName} | {siteConfig.name}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={projectSummary} />
  </head>

  <body class="bg-background text-foreground">
    <Header />

    <main class="pt-24 pb-16">
      <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-10">
        {/* Header */}
        <header class="space-y-3">
          <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-blue-500">{pageType}</p>

          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-100">
            {projectName}
          </h1>

          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-400">{projectTagline}</p>
          <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-400">{projectSummary}</p>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 space-y-2">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-semibold">Context</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              Built as a fast prototype plan after speaking with Erin Martin (HR) and Drake Miller (Process Team) at the ASU career fair.
              The goal is to demonstrate an intern deliverable aligned to Amkor product engineering needs for product analytics, utilization,
              and profitability workflows using LLM tools.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              This page is public but unlisted. It is intended for Amkor reviewers and interview discussion.
            </p>
          </div>
        </header>

        {/* Posting alignment */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Role Alignment</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            This case study is designed to map directly to the Product Engineer Intern posting for the Advanced Flip Chip BGA and Chiplets product team.
            The emphasis is product analytics, Industry 4.0 style monitoring, and communication outputs that support decision making.
          </p>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 space-y-3">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-semibold">Direct mapping to posting responsibilities</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li><span class="font-medium">Product analytics to strategy:</span> roll up operational data into decision oriented KPIs and recommendations.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Industry 4.0 workflow:</span> use LLM tools to monitor and review profitability drivers and utilization constraints.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Pricing and volume allocation support:</span> generate a structured decision brief based on margin and capacity signals.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Equipment utilization:</span> identify where capacity is constrained and what is driving downtime and yield loss.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Communication:</span> produce an executive ready slide outline from the same analysis output.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* Intern deliverables */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Intern Deliverables</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            If selected, this is the deliverable set I would aim to produce early, then refine with real Amkor data sources and feedback from product engineering and process teams.
          </p>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 space-y-3">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-semibold">Deliverables that match the posting</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li><span class="font-medium">Weekly profitability snapshot:</span> margin proxies driven by yield, scrap, rework, downtime, and throughput.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Utilization and capacity summary:</span> where constraints are, trend direction, and likely drivers.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Downtime triage SITREP generator:</span> consistent incident summary with recommended next actions and confidence.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">PowerPoint ready slide outline:</span> executive review format generated from the same data and SITREP.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">Recommendation memo:</span> proposed next steps and roadmap based on what worked and what data is missing.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* Why */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Why</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            Manufacturing and product teams often spend time converting scattered signals into decisions.
            Data exists, but triage, interpretation, and communication slow the loop.
            This project proposes a private LLM workflow that turns operational signals into a structured SITREP and an executive ready slide outline.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Goal:</span> reduce time from signal to decision and improve clarity of recommendations.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Goal:</span> standardize reporting so weekly reviews are consistent and comparable.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Constraints:</span> privacy, auditability, and messy real world logs.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        {/* What */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">What</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            A Manufacturing and Product Ops Copilot that ingests operational metrics and event logs, computes a small set of decision KPIs,
            then uses a local LLM to generate two outputs:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Downtime triage SITREP:</span> what happened, impact, likely drivers, and recommended actions.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Slide outline:</span> an executive ready structure that can be pasted into PowerPoint.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100">Key requirements</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Privacy first:</span> runs locally with no external data egress by default.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Actionable outputs:</span> recommendations tied to utilization and profitability impacts.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Explainability:</span> each recommendation includes supporting evidence and data gaps.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Fast iteration:</span> usable for daily triage and weekly review.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 space-y-2">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-semibold">Privacy posture</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>Default mode is local inference with no external LLM provider access to raw data.</li>
              <li>Optional stretch is a gated redaction and escalation pattern, not the core system.</li>
              <li>Outputs are designed for auditability with visible inputs and stated uncertainty.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* Architecture */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Architecture</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            The architecture is intentionally simple for reliability and privacy. A data layer produces KPIs.
            A local LLM generates structured outputs. A UI presents the SITREP, key charts, and a one click slide outline.
          </p>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">High level architecture diagram</p>

            <div class="w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-950/40">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 1200 420" role="img" aria-label="Ops Copilot architecture diagram" class="w-full h-auto">
                <defs>
                  <style>
                    .box { fill: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.6); stroke: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.35); stroke-width: 2; rx: 18; }
                    .txt { fill: rgba(226, 232, 240, 0.95); font: 18px ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto; }
                    .sub { fill: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.95); font: 14px ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto; }
                    .arrow { stroke: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.85); stroke-width: 3; marker-end: url(#m); }
                  </style>
                  <marker id="m" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                    <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.85)"></path>
                  </marker>
                </defs>

                <rect class="box" x="40" y="60" width="300" height="130" />
                <text class="txt" x="70" y="100">Factory signals</text>
                <text class="sub" x="70" y="130">events, alarms, downtime</text>
                <text class="sub" x="70" y="155">yield, scrap, rework</text>
                <text class="sub" x="70" y="180">throughput, utilization</text>

                <rect class="box" x="420" y="60" width="330" height="130" />
                <text class="txt" x="450" y="100">Metrics layer</text>
                <text class="sub" x="450" y="130">KPI rollups and features</text>
                <text class="sub" x="450" y="155">profitability and capacity impact</text>
                <text class="sub" x="450" y="180">data quality checks</text>

                <rect class="box" x="820" y="60" width="340" height="130" />
                <text class="txt" x="850" y="100">Local LLM engine</text>
                <text class="sub" x="850" y="130">private inference, no egress</text>
                <text class="sub" x="850" y="155">structured SITREP generation</text>
                <text class="sub" x="850" y="180">slide outline generation</text>

                <rect class="box" x="220" y="240" width="360" height="140" />
                <text class="txt" x="250" y="280">UI and reporting</text>
                <text class="sub" x="250" y="310">incident list, charts, SITREP</text>
                <text class="sub" x="250" y="335">evidence and confidence</text>
                <text class="sub" x="250" y="360">copy to PowerPoint</text>

                <rect class="box" x="660" y="240" width="500" height="140" />
                <text class="txt" x="690" y="280">Optional stretch</text>
                <text class="sub" x="690" y="310">policy gated redaction and escalation</text>
                <text class="sub" x="690" y="335">only if approved, only if sanitized</text>
                <text class="sub" x="690" y="360">external model never sees raw identifiers</text>

                <line class="arrow" x1="340" y1="125" x2="420" y2="125" />
                <line class="arrow" x1="750" y1="125" x2="820" y2="125" />
                <line class="arrow" x1="990" y1="190" x2="450" y2="240" />
                <line class="arrow" x1="580" y1="310" x2="660" y2="310" />
              </svg>
            </div>

            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-3">
              Default path is local inference. The optional stretch path is a gated redaction and escalation pattern.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* Execution plan with dates */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Execution Plan</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            This plan is scoped to demonstrate capability quickly, then leave a clean foundation for expansion using real internal data sources.
          </p>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 space-y-3">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 font-semibold">Milestones</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li><span class="font-medium">2026-02-13:</span> case study page published and application submitted.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">2026-02-14 to 2026-02-15:</span> prototype implementation with synthetic dataset and UI.</li>
              <li><span class="font-medium">2026-02-16:</span> demo walkthrough video, updated results section, and polished outputs.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* Testing criteria */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">Evaluation Criteria</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Time to SITREP:</span> generate a structured incident summary in under 60 seconds.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Decision clarity:</span> recommendations include next actions, confidence, and missing data.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Presentation readiness:</span> slide outline can be pasted into PowerPoint with minimal edits.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Privacy:</span> default operation requires no external data sharing.</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">Demo link (placeholder)</p>
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-dashed border-slate-700 p-4 text-sm text-slate-400">
              Video will be added here after recording.
              <div class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-500">
                Target: 60 to 90 second walkthrough showing incident selection, SITREP output, and slide outline output.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        {/* Next steps */}
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-100">What I&apos;d Do Next</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>Add evidence citations per recommendation, including which metrics triggered the conclusion.</li>
            <li>Add role based views: engineering manager summary, engineer handoff, and weekly review view.</li>
            <li>Add utilization and profitability decision templates for weekly review workflows.</li>
            <li>Integrate automation triggers compatible with Copilot and Power Automate style workflows.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        {/* Back link */}
        <div class="pt-4">
          <a
            href="/projects"
            class="text-sm text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline-offset-2 hover:underline"
          >
            ‚Üê Back to all projects
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
